{
  "local_port": 55122,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I increase font size in Quora?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Quora does not provide a direct option to increase the font size within its platform. However, you can adjust the font size on Quora using a few workarounds:\n\n1. **Browser Zoom:**\n   - Most web browsers allow you to zoom in on web pages, which effectively increases the font size.\n   - On Windows, you can usually zoom in by pressing `Ctrl` and `+` (plus sign). To zoom out, press `Ctrl` and `-` (minus sign).\n   - On macOS, use `Command` and `+` (plus sign) to zoom in, and `Command` and `-` (minus sign) to zoom out.\n   - You can reset the zoom level to default by pressing `Ctrl` + `0` (or `Command` + `0` on a Mac).\n\n2. **Browser Settings:**\n   - Some browsers let you adjust the default font size:\n     - In Chrome, go to `Settings` > `Appearance` > `Font size`.\n     - In Firefox, go to `Options` > `General` > `Language and Appearance` > `Fonts and Colors`.\n     - In Safari, go to `Preferences` > `Advanced` > select `Never use font sizes smaller than`.\n\n3. **Reader Mode:**\n   - Some browsers offer a \"reader mode\" that simplifies the page layout and lets you customize font sizes.\n   - In Chrome and Firefox, this is typically found as an icon in the address bar when it's available.\n\n4. **Extensions/Plugins:**\n   - Consider installing browser extensions or add-ons that allow for more control over text size and appearance.\n   - Search for extensions like \"Zoom\" or \"Accessibility\" in your browser's extension store.\n\n5. **Operating System Settings:**\n   - You can also adjust overall display settings in your operating system for larger fonts across all applications.\n   - On Windows, go to `Settings` > `Ease of Access` > `Display`.\n   - On macOS, go to `System Preferences` > `Displays`.\n\nTry using one or a combination of these methods to increase the font size on Quora. Keep in mind that these adjustments will affect other websites as well and might not be specific to Quora alone.",
